# Rocket.new — Project Architecture Reference

> The exact folder structure Rocket generates. Use this to understand the codebase before touching anything.

---

## Complete File Tree — Next.js (TypeScript) — Standard Rocket Project

```
project-root/
│
├── middleware.ts                    # ← CRITICAL: at root, not in /app
│                                    #   Calls updateSession() on every request
│                                    #   Missing = sessions never refresh = auth breaks
│
├── app/
│   ├── layout.tsx                   # Root layout — wraps ALL pages
│   │                                # Contains: <html>, <body>, global providers
│   │                                # NOT for page-specific data fetching
│   │
│   ├── page.tsx                     # Landing page (/)
│   ├── globals.css                  # Global styles + Tailwind @layer imports
│   │
│   ├── (auth)/                      # Route GROUP — no URL segment added
│   │   ├── login/
│   │   │   └── page.tsx             # /login
│   │   ├── signup/
│   │   │   └── page.tsx             # /signup
│   │   └── reset-password/
│   │       └── page.tsx             # /reset-password
│   │
│   ├── (protected)/                 # Route GROUP — all routes inside are protected
│   │   ├── layout.tsx               # Auth check here — getUser() → redirect if null
│   │   ├── dashboard/
│   │   │   ├── page.tsx             # /dashboard
│   │   │   └── loading.tsx          # Auto-shown by Next.js while page.tsx loads
│   │   ├── settings/
│   │   │   └── page.tsx             # /settings
│   │   └── profile/
│   │       └── page.tsx             # /profile
│   │
│   ├── auth/
│   │   └── callback/
│   │       └── route.ts             # ← CRITICAL: OAuth + magic link exchange
│   │                                #   Calls exchangeCodeForSession(code)
│   │                                #   Missing = OAuth always fails
│   │
│   └── api/
│       ├── stripe/
│       │   └── checkout/
│       │       └── route.ts         # POST: creates Stripe checkout session
│       └── webhooks/
│           └── stripe/
│               └── route.ts         # POST: handles Stripe events
│                                    # MUST use request.text() not request.json()
│
├── components/
│   ├── ui/                          # Base UI: button, input, card, badge, etc.
│   │   ├── button.tsx               # shadcn/ui or custom Rocket components
│   │   ├── input.tsx
│   │   └── card.tsx
│   ├── layout/
│   │   ├── navbar.tsx               # Navigation — often 'use client' for mobile menu
│   │   ├── sidebar.tsx
│   │   └── footer.tsx
│   └── [feature]/                   # Feature-specific components
│       └── [component].tsx
│
├── lib/
│   └── supabase/
│       ├── client.ts                # Browser client — 'use client' components ONLY
│       ├── server.ts                # Server client — Server Components, Route Handlers, Actions
│       └── middleware.ts            # updateSession() — called by root middleware.ts
│
├── supabase/                        # ← Rocket generates this, often overlooked
│   ├── migrations/                  # SQL migration files — pushed to Supabase
│   │   ├── 001_initial_schema.sql   # Push via Rocket UI or paste into Supabase SQL Editor
│   │   ├── 002_add_profiles.sql
│   │   └── [timestamp]_[name].sql
│   └── functions/                   # Edge Functions (if any were created)
│       └── [function-name]/
│           └── index.ts
│
├── public/                          # Static assets served directly
│   ├── images/
│   └── _redirects                   # React SPA routing fix (Vite projects only)
│
├── .env.local                       # Local env vars — NEVER committed, NEVER auto-synced to Netlify
├── .env.example                     # Template — safe to commit
├── next.config.ts                   # Next.js configuration
├── tailwind.config.ts               # Tailwind — always darkMode: 'class'
├── tsconfig.json                    # TypeScript — includes @/* path alias
└── package.json
```

