## Dependency Map — What Imports What

Understanding this prevents breaking callers when editing a file.

```
middleware.ts
  └─ imports: lib/supabase/middleware.ts → updateSession()
               (Do NOT import server.ts or client.ts here)

app/[route]/page.tsx (Server Component)
  └─ imports: lib/supabase/server.ts → createClient()
               components/[feature]/...
               lib/supabase/[queries].ts (if extracted)

app/[route]/[component].tsx (Client Component — 'use client')
  └─ imports: lib/supabase/client.ts → createClient()
               (NOT server.ts — causes SSR/cookie errors)

app/api/[route]/route.ts (Route Handler)
  └─ imports: lib/supabase/server.ts → createClient()
               stripe (if payment route)

lib/supabase/middleware.ts
  └─ imports: @supabase/ssr → createServerClient
               next/server → NextResponse, NextRequest

lib/supabase/server.ts
  └─ imports: @supabase/ssr → createServerClient
               next/headers → cookies

lib/supabase/client.ts
  └─ imports: @supabase/ssr → createBrowserClient
```

**Ripple effect rule**: If you edit `lib/supabase/server.ts` or `lib/supabase/client.ts`, every Server Component and Client Component is affected. Always check callers before changing these files.

