## What Rocket NEVER Generates (Always Add Manually)

These are consistently missing from every Rocket project and must be added when needed:

| What | Where | Why Needed |
|---|---|---|
| Rate limiting on API routes | `app/api/[route]/route.ts` | AI/LLM endpoints get abused without it |
| Input validation (Zod) | Server Actions, Route Handlers | Rocket generates no input validation |
| Error logging (Sentry/etc.) | `app/layout.tsx`, `app/error.tsx` | No error tracking by default |
| Database indexes | `supabase/migrations/` | Tables have no indexes — slow at scale |
| Canonical URLs | `app/layout.tsx` metadata | Needed for SEO to avoid duplicate content |
| `robots.txt` | `public/robots.txt` | Not generated by default |
| `sitemap.xml` | `app/sitemap.ts` | Must be added manually |
| CSRF protection | API routes | Not generated — use `next-csrf` or Origin check |
| Image optimization config | `next.config.ts` | Remote image domains must be whitelisted |

### Adding Image Domains (Most Common Missing Config)
```typescript
// next.config.ts
const nextConfig = {
  images: {
    remotePatterns: [
      {
        protocol: 'https',
        hostname: '[your-supabase-id].supabase.co',
        pathname: '/storage/v1/object/public/**',
      },
    ],
  },
}
```

### Adding Rate Limiting to AI Endpoints
```typescript
// Simple rate limit using Supabase
import { createClient } from '@/lib/supabase/server'

export async function POST(request: Request) {
  const supabase = await createClient()
  const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser()
  if (!user) return new Response('Unauthorized', { status: 401 })
  
  // Check usage count for today
  const today = new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0]
  const { count } = await supabase
    .from('ai_usage')
    .select('*', { count: 'exact', head: true })
    .eq('user_id', user.id)
    .gte('created_at', today)
  
  if ((count ?? 0) >= 50) {
    return new Response('Rate limit exceeded', { status: 429 })
  }
  // ... rest of handler
}
```

